== Japanese ==
[[Image:Japanese Katakana I.png|thumb|right|Katakana character イ]]
===Etymology===
Simplified in the [[w:Heian period|Heian period]] from the ''[[man'yōgana]]'' ([[万葉仮名]]) kanji [[伊]] (''i''), taken from the left part of the character.

===Katakana character===
'''イ''' (''i'')

# the [i] phoneme, typically in words of non-Japanese origins
#: The second character of the first column of the [[katakana]] [[syllabary]], it is analogous to [[い]] (''i'') in the [[hiragana]] syllabary. The previous katakana character is [[ア]] (''a'') and the next is [[ウ]] (''u'').

